Philippine Stocks: Alliance Global, Belle, Leisure & Resorts

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-04-05T03:45:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/philippine-stocks-alliance-global-belle-leisure-resorts.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:10 a.m. local time.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 0.8 percent to
4,177.08.  Alliance Global Group Inc. (AGI)  , owner of the company
that operates  Manila ’s biggest casino, fell 5.2 percent to 11.38
pesos, bound for the sharpest loss since Jan. 19. Alliance and
its unit  Megaworld Corp. (MEG)  sold 872 million shares of the company
at 11.16 pesos each through a private placement, a stock
exchange filing showed. That’s a 7 percent discount to
yesterday’s closing price.  Leisure & Resorts World Corp. (LR)  , which will operate a
casino in Manila, advanced 2.2 percent to 10.46 pesos, set for
the highest close since Oct. 15, 1999, after the company said it
signed agreements for the sale of shares through a so-called
private placement that will raise 1.13 billion pesos.  Leisure said it will use part of the proceeds for the
gaming complex that it will operate and manage for  Belle Corp. (BEL) 
. Belle rose 1.1 percent to 5.50 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
